{
  "stem": "25639.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How did your parents cope with the change in language?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not quite as well as children, but as I remember, they also started phasing out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was much easier for them to speak Hungarian, because they were part of the Austro-Hungarian empire, and they spoke Hungarian prior to the area becoming Czechoslovakia in World War I, when the Austro-Hungarian empire broke up.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Traditionally.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- Mother lit the Shabbat candles, and we said the bracha-- the prayer-- and then my dad would say [NON-ENGLISH], and we had traditional foods-- wonderful foods.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right, we started out usually with fish, and we had chicken and farfel, and salad-- which consisted of, not the tossed salad that we have here, but cut up vegetables.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we would have [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] chicken soup, of course, which I forgot.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And-- and some sort of compote for dessert.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And wine, of course-- wine went with every meal, including breakfast.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] In the wintertime, we would make mulled wine, and before I went off to school, I-- I would have a glass of mulled wine.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nobody was drunk in my family, ever.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we-- we just enjoyed wine-- red wine, particularly, at the time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's a good question.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I went to a public school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Elementary school was all public in our area, and we were excused during the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] it's-- it was called, which is religious hour.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think it was a couple of hours, or an hour and a half.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm not sure exactly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we were excused and-- because we were Jewish, and my parents wanted us to learn Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And just a block away was the synagogue from-- from-- from the public school, from the elementary school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were learning-- we learned Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
